  "prompt": "How do I reset my WeChat password?",
  "response": "To reset your WeChat password, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open WeChat**: Launch the WeChat app on your device.\n\n2. **Go to the Login Screen**: If you are logged in, you will need to log out first. Tap on \"Me\" (or \"My\") at the bottom right, then tap on your profile picture, scroll down, and select \"Log out.\"\n\n3. **Select \"Forgot Password\"**: On the login screen, tap on \"Log in,\" and then select the option that says \"Forgot password?\" or \"Reset Password.\"\n\n4. **Enter Your Phone Number**: Input the phone number linked to your WeChat account. If you\u2019ve set up email recovery, you might have the option to use your email instead.\n\n5. **Verification**: WeChat will send a verification code to your registered phone number or email. Check your messages and enter the code when prompted.\n\n6. **Set a New Password**: After verifying your identity, you will be prompted to create a new password. Make sure it\u2019s strong and memorable.\n\n7. **Login with New Password**: Once you\u2019ve set your new password, return to the login screen and enter your credentials to access your account.\n\nIf you have trouble, ensure that you're connected to the internet and that the phone number or email you entered is the one associated with your WeChat account. If you encounter persistent issues, you can contact WeChat support for further assistance.",
